{"title_page": "Pondok Cabe Airport", "text_new": "{{Infobox airport\n|name                = '''Pondok Cabe Airport'''\n|nativename          = Bandar Udara Pondok Cabe\n|nativename-a        = \n|nativename-r        = \n|image               =\n|image-width         = \n|caption             = Pondok Cabe\n|IATA                = PCB\n|ICAO                = WIHP\n|type                = Military/Public\n|owner               = [[Pelita Air|PT Pelita Air Service]]\n|operator            = [[Pelita Air|PT Pelita Air Service]]\n|city-served         = [[South Tangerang]], [[South Jakarta]] and [[Depok]]\n|location            = [[South Tangerang]], [[Banten]]\n|elevation-f         = \n|elevation-m         = \n|r1-number           = 18/36\n|r1-length-f         = 6516\n|r1-length-m         = 1986\n|r1-surface          = [[Asphalt]]\n|website             = \n|metric-elev         = 61\n|metric-rwy          = \n|stat-year           = \n|stat1-header        = \n|stat1-data          = \n|stat2-header        = \n|stat2-data          = \n|footnotes           = \n|coordinates         =\n {{coord|6|20|13.05|S|106|45|53.99|E|display=title,inline}}\n|pushpin_map         = Indonesia_Depok#Indonesia_Java#Indonesia\n|pushpin_map_caption = Location in [[Depok]], [[Java]] and [[Indonesia]]\n|pushpin_label       = PCB\n}}\n'''Pondok Cabe Airport''' ([[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]: ''Bandar Udara Pondok Cabe'') is a mixed civilian and military airport in the Pondok Cabe, Pamulang, [[South Tangerang]]. The airport is owned by the state oil company [[Pertamina]] and operated by [[Pelita Air Service]], which also owned Indopelita Aircraft Services that has a maintenance hangar at this airport. Currently, Pondok Cabe does not handle regular airline traffic. Other than serving as the [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|Maintenance, repair and overhaul]] base for Pelita Air Service, the airport is also the home of the Aviation Wing of the [[Indonesian National Police]], [[CASA 212]] equipped-Skadron Udara 21/Serba Guna of the [[Indonesian Army]] and Naval Aviation (Puspenerbal) of [[Indonesian Navy]], as well as Portela Jaya [[Light-sport aircraft]] hangar.\n\nPondok Cabe Airport serves Ciputat, [[Cinere|Cinere, Depok]], other parts of [[Depok]] and districts in [[South Jakarta]]. {{Airport codes|PCB|WIHP}}. The airport is located in South Tangerang and not far from the border of Cinere in Depok, Pamulang, West and East Ciputat in South Tangerang, and Cilandak and Jagakarsa in South Jakarta. It has a runway with a length of 1,986 m (6,516&nbsp;ft).\n\nAviation Agencies Australia used to plan to invest US$100 million to develop Pondok Cabe to a commercial airport, by building a new terminal and lengthening the runway to 2,500 m which was planned to be started in 2009.<ref>[http://www.tempointeraktif.com/hg/jakarta/2008/04/22/brk,20080422-121738,id.html Tempointeraktif.com - Bandara Pondok Cabe Direncanakan Akan Dikomersilkan<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924131023/http://www.tempointeraktif.com/hg/jakarta/2008/04/22/brk,20080422-121738,id.html |date=2015-09-24 }}</ref>\n\nThe airport serves as a maintenance base for [[Pelita Air Service]].\n\nIndonesian flag carrier [[Garuda Indonesia]] plans to open a base at Pondok Cabe Airport by the end of 2016,<ref>http://www.jpnn.com/read/2016/04/18/385173/Rencana-Garuda-Terbang-ke-Cilacap-Tergantung-Pondok-Cabe-</ref> offering flights to cities in Java, Sumatra and Kalimantan using [[ATR 72-600]] aircraft.<ref>http://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20151113141246-92-91472/garuda-layani-penerbangan-dari-pondok-cabe-mulai-tahun-depan/</ref> The government has given approval to Garuda Indonesia to, once the airport opens to scheduled servies, provide daily flights to six destinations: [[Radin Inten II Airport|Bandar Lampung]] and [[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport|Palembang]] on Sumatra, [[Iskandar Airport|Pangkalan Bun]] in [[Central Kalimantan]], and [[Achmad Yani International Airport|Semarang]], [[Adisucipto International Airport|Yogyakarta]], and [[Adisumarmo International Airport|Solo]] on Java.<ref>http://ekbis.sindonews.com/read/1096118/34/garuda-buka-enam-rute-penerbangan-dari-bandara-pondok-cabe-1459075447</ref>\n\n==Airlines and Destinations==\n{{airport-dest-list\n<!-- According to WP:AIRPORTS \"Do not separate flights into domestic (national) and international.\" -->\n| [[EastIndo]] |'''Charter:''' [[Sultan Syarif Kasim II International Airport|Pekanbaru]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Pelita Air Service]] |'''Charter:''' [[Pinang Kampai Airport|Dumai]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==References==\n* [http://worldaerodata.com/wad.cgi?id=ID57783&sch=pondok+cabe]\n{{reflist}}\n{{Airports in Indonesia}}\n\n{{Portal|Aviation}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:South Tangerang]]\n[[Category:Airports in Banten]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-airport-stub}}\n{{Banten-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox airport\n|name                = '''Pondok Cabe Airport'''\n|nativename          = Bandar Udara Pondok Cabe\n|nativename-a        = \n|nativename-r        = \n|image               =\n|image-width         = \n|caption             = Pondok Cabe\n|IATA                = PCB\n|ICAO                = WIHP\n|type                = Military/Public\n|owner               = [[Pelita Air|PT Pelita Air Service]]\n|operator            = [[Pelita Air|PT Pelita Air Service]]\n|city-served         = [[South Tangerang]], [[South Jakarta]] and [[Depok]]\n|location            = [[South Tangerang]], [[Banten]]\n|elevation-f         = \n|elevation-m         = \n|r1-number           = 18/36\n|r1-length-f         = 6516\n|r1-length-m         = 1986\n|r1-surface          = [[Asphalt]]\n|website             = \n|metric-elev         = 61\n|metric-rwy          = \n|stat-year           = \n|stat1-header        = \n|stat1-data          = \n|stat2-header        = \n|stat2-data          = \n|footnotes           = \n|coordinates         =\n {{coord|6|20|13.05|S|106|45|53.99|E|display=title,inline}}\n|pushpin_map         = Indonesia_Depok#Indonesia_Java#Indonesia\n|pushpin_map_caption = Location in [[Depok]], [[Java]] and [[Indonesia]]\n|pushpin_label       = PCB\n}}\n'''Pondok Cabe Airport''' ([[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]: ''Bandar Udara Pondok Cabe'') is a mixed civilian and military airport in the Pondok Cabe, Pamulang, [[South Tangerang]]. The airport is owned by the state oil company [[Pertamina]] and operated by [[Pelita Air Service]], which also owned Indopelita Aircraft Services that has a maintenance hangar at this airport. Currently, Pondok Cabe does not handle regular airline traffic. Other than serving as the [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|Maintenance, repair and overhaul]] base for Pelita Air Service, the airport is also the home of the Aviation Wing of the [[Indonesian National Police]], [[CASA 212]] equipped-Skadron Udara 21/Serba Guna of the [[Indonesian Army]] and Naval Aviation (Puspenerbal) of [[Indonesian Navy]], as well as Portela Jaya [[Light-sport aircraft]] hangar.\n\nPondok Cabe Airport serves Ciputat, [[Cinere|Cinere, Depok]], other parts of [[Depok]] and districts in [[South Jakarta]]. {{Airport codes|PCB|WIHP}}. The airport is located in South Tangerang and not far from the border of Cinere in Depok, Pamulang, West and East Ciputat in South Tangerang, and Cilandak and Jagakarsa in South Jakarta. It has a runway with a length of 1,986 m (6,516&nbsp;ft).\n\nAviation Agencies Australia used to plan to invest US$100 million to develop Pondok Cabe to a commercial airport, by building a new terminal and lengthening the runway to 2,500 m which was planned to be started in 2009.<ref>[http://www.tempointeraktif.com/hg/jakarta/2008/04/22/brk,20080422-121738,id.html Tempointeraktif.com - Bandara Pondok Cabe Direncanakan Akan Dikomersilkan<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924131023/http://www.tempointeraktif.com/hg/jakarta/2008/04/22/brk,20080422-121738,id.html |date=2015-09-24 }}</ref>\n\nThe airport serves as a maintenance base for [[Pelita Air Service]].\n\nIndonesian flag carrier [[Garuda Indonesia]] plans to open a base at Pondok Cabe Airport by the end of 2016,<ref>http://www.jpnn.com/read/2016/04/18/385173/Rencana-Garuda-Terbang-ke-Cilacap-Tergantung-Pondok-Cabe-</ref> offering flights to cities in Java, Sumatra and Kalimantan using [[ATR 72-600]] aircraft.<ref>http://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20151113141246-92-91472/garuda-layani-penerbangan-dari-pondok-cabe-mulai-tahun-depan/</ref> The government has given approval to Garuda Indonesia to, once the airport opens to scheduled servies, provide daily flights to six destinations: [[Radin Inten II Airport|Bandar Lampung]] and [[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport|Palembang]] on Sumatra, [[Iskandar Airport|Pangkalan Bun]] in [[Central Kalimantan]], and [[Achmad Yani International Airport|Semarang]], [[Adisucipto International Airport|Yogyakarta]], and [[Adisumarmo International Airport|Solo]] on Java.<ref>http://ekbis.sindonews.com/read/1096118/34/garuda-buka-enam-rute-penerbangan-dari-bandara-pondok-cabe-1459075447</ref>\n\n==Airlines and Destinations==\n{{airport-dest-list\n<!-- According to WP:AIRPORTS \"Do not separate flights into domestic (national) and international.\" -->\n| [[EastIndo]] |'''Charter:''' [[Sultan Syarif Kasim II International Airport|Pekanbaru]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Pelita Air Service]] |'''Charter:''' [[Pinang Kampai Airport|Dumai]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==References==\n* [http://worldaerodata.com/wad.cgi?id=ID57783&sch=pondok+cabe]\n{{reflist}}\n{{Airports in Indonesia}}\n\n{{Portal|Aviation}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in Banten]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-airport-stub}}\n{{Banten-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:South TangerangusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pondok_Cabe_Airport"}
