{"title_page": "Nikolaos Ioannidis", "text_new": "{{for|the Greek rower|Nikolaos Ioannidis (rower)}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|image               = \n|image_size          = \n|caption             = \n|fullname            = \n|birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1994|4|26}}\n|birth_place         = [[Remscheid]], Germany\n|height              = {{height|m=1.88}}\n|position            = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n|currentclub         = [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]\n|clubnumber          = 99\n|youthyears1         = \n|youthclubs1         = [[Pandramaikos F.C.|Pandramaikos]]\n|youthyears2         = {{0|0000}}\u20132012\n|youthclubs2         = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|years1              = 2012\u20132016\n|clubs1              = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|caps1               = 0\n|goals1              = 0\n|years2              = 2013\u20132014\n|clubs2              = \u2192 [[Hansa Rostock]] (loan)\n|caps2               = 30\n|goals2              = 6\n|years3              = 2014\u20132015\n|clubs3              = \u2192 [[PEC Zwolle|Zwolle]] (loan)\n|caps3               = 4\n|goals3              = 0\n|years4              = 2015\u20132016\n|clubs4              = \u2192 [[Borussia Dortmund II]] (loan)\n|caps4               = 23\n|goals4              = 2\n|years5              = 2016\u20132017\n|clubs5              = [[Asteras Tripoli F.C.|Asteras Tripolis]]\n|caps5               = 36\n|goals5              = 6\n|years6              = 2017\u20132018\n|clubs6              = [[Di\u00f3sgy\u0151ri VTK|Di\u00f3sgy\u0151r]]\n|caps6               = 35\n|goals6              = 5\n|years7              = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs7              = [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo|Mar\u00edtimo]]\n|caps7               = 0\n|goals7              = 0\n|years8              = 2019\n|clubs8              = [[Doxa Drama F.C.|Doxa Drama]]\n|caps8               = 9\n|goals8              = 5\n|years9              = 2020\u2013\n|clubs9              = [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]\n|caps9               = 5\n|goals9              = 2\n|nationalyears1      =  2010\u20132012\n|nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-17 football team|Greece U17]] \n|nationalcaps1       = 4\n|nationalgoals1      = 0\n|nationalyears2      =  2012\u20132013\n|nationalteam2 = [[Greece national under-18 football team|Greece U18]] \n|nationalcaps2       = 3\n|nationalgoals2      = 0\n|nationalyears3      =  2012\u20132015\n|nationalteam3 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U19]] \n|nationalcaps3       = 10\n|nationalgoals3      = 3\n|nationalyears4      =  2015\u20132016\n|nationalteam4 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U21]] \n|nationalcaps4       = 11\n|nationalgoals4      = 7\n|medaltemplates      = \n|club-update         = 9 February 2020\n|nationalteam-update = 29 March 2016\n}}\n'''Nikolaos Ioannidis''' ({{lang-gr|\u039d\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb\u03b1\u03bf\u03c2 \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; born 26 April 1994) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Super League Greece 2|Super League 2]] club [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nAlthough born in Germany, Nikos Ioannidis moved to Greece at a very early age and made his first football steps in [[Pandramaikos F.C.|Pandramaikos]]. Olympiacos initially showed interest and signed the player, who was included in the youth team of Olympiacos.\n\n===Olympiacos===\nOn 18 April 2013, he made his debut for Olympiacos in a 6-2 [[Greek Cup]] win against [[Panthrakikos F.C.|Panthrakikos]], coming off the bench to replace [[Kostas Mitroglou]] after 69 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.woop.gr/content/107517/axehasto-debouto-gia-ioannide-photo|publisher=woop.gr |script-title=el:\u0391\u03be\u03ad\u03c7\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03c4\u03b5\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03cd\u03c4\u03bf \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7! (photo)|language=el|date=19 April 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629151020/http://www.woop.gr/content/107517/axehasto-debouto-gia-ioannide-photo|archivedate=29 June 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Hansa Rostock====\nOn July 2013 Germany's third division club [[Hansa Rostock]] has reached an agreement with the Greek football champion [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiakos]] on a perpetual strategic partnership and borrowed in the course of the cooperation of the Greek Under-19 national team Nikolaos Ioannidis for a year. ''\"In Greece there are no full-scale substructure in the form of second teams,\"'' said Rostock's sporting director ''Uwe Vester'' on Monday. ''\"At this point we come into play, because highly talented, young players can so help us on our way and simultaneously collect valuable experience for their own careers.\"''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rp-online.de/sport/fussball/dritteliga/hansa-rostock-leiht-nikolaos-ioannidis-aus-aid-1.3540169|publisher=rp-online.de|title=Hansa Rostock leiht Nikolaos Ioannidis aus|trans-title=Hansa Rostock lends out Nikolaos Ioannidis|language=de|date=15 July 2013|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to PEC Zwolle====\nAfter the departure of [[Fred Benson]] and [[Guyon Fernandez]],  [[PEC Zwolle]] was shy about attacking reinforcements. Eventually the cup holder hires Ioannidis who will plays on loan for the club in the Dutch [[Eredivisie]] since the season 2014/2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/pec-zwolle-neemt-ioannidis-over-van-olympiakos.htm|publisher=www.vi.nl|title=PEC Zwolle neemt Ioannidis over van Olympiakos|language=nl|date=10 July 2014|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.olympiacos.org/article/38102/daneikos-stin-tsbole-o-ioannidis|publisher=Olympiacos.org|script-title=el:\u0394\u03b1\u03bd\u03b5\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a4\u03c3\u03b2\u03cc\u03bb\u03b5 \u03bf \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|trans-title=Ioannidis is on a loan to Tsvele|language=el|date=10 July 2014|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> His loan was ended on 9 January 2015, after a lack of prospect.<ref>[http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/pec-zwolle/23539935/__PEC_Zwolle_stuurt_huurling_weg__.html PEC Zwolle stuurt huurling weg] (Dutch). 9 January 2015. Retrieved 11 September 2017.</ref>\n\n====Loan to Borussia Dortmund====\nOn 15 January 2015, Ioannidis is back in the [[3. Liga]]. The striker, who played last season 30 games for [[Hansa Rostock]] (six goals), signed a contract with [[Borussia Dortmund II]]. This provides that the 20-year-old Greek until June 2016 on loan from [[Olympiacos]] Piraeus. Ioannidis was on loan to [[PEC Zwolle]] played only four league games and a game in the [[Europa League]]. He is still under contract with [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiakos]] until 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liga3-online.de/dortmund-ii-leiht-ex-hansa-spieler-nikolaos-ioannidis-aus/|title=Dortmund II leiht Ex-Hansa-Spieler Nikolaos Ioannidis aus|trans-title=Dortmund II lends ex-Hansa player: Nikolaos Ioannidis|author=Julian Koch|language=de|date=15 January 2015|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Asteras Tripolis===\n[[Asteras Tripolis]] officially announced the signing of 22-year-old Greek striker Nikos Ioannidis until the summer of 2018, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sdna.gr/news-english/article/162309/asteras-tripolis-announce-ioannidis-signing|title=Asteras Tripolis announce Ioannidis' signing|date=29 January 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\nIn his 10th appearance with the club, in a 2-1 home game against [[Veria F.C.|Veria]], he scored a brace, sealing the victory for his club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/ellada/SuperLeague/nikh-xwris-antikrisma-gia-astera-2-1-th-veroia.4013667.html|script-title=el:\u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03b7 \u03c7\u03c9\u03c1\u03af\u03c2 \u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03ba\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u0391\u03c3\u03c4\u03ad\u03c1\u03b1, 2-1 \u03c4\u03b7 \u0392\u03ad\u03c1\u03bf\u03b9\u03b1|trans-title=Win without a hit: Asteras 2-1 Veroia|language=el|date=17 April 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 1 July 2017, Ioannidis had mutually solved his contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/AsterasTripolis/eyxaristhse-ton-astera-o-iwannidhs.4746411.html |script-title=el:\u0395\u03c5\u03c7\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0391\u03c3\u03c4\u03ad\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bf \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|trans-title=Ioannidis thanks Astero|language=el|date=1 July 2017|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Di\u00f3sgy\u0151r===\n[[Di\u00f3sgy\u0151ri VTK|Di\u00f3sgy\u0151r]] officially announced the signing of the Greek striker until the summer of 2020, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.enwsi.gr/podosfairo/gia-tria-chronia-stin-dvtk-o-ioannidis-pic/|script-title=el:\u0393\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd DVTK \u03bf \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2!|trans-title=Ioannidis signed a three year contract with DVTK!|language=el|date=6 July 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/magyaros-o-nikos-iwannidhs.4752813.html|script-title=el:\"\u039c\u03b1\u03b3\u03c5\u03ac\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2\" \u03bf \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf\u03c2 \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|trans-title=\"Magyaros\" by Nikos Ioannidis|language=el|date=6 July 2016|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 16 September 2017, he scored his first goal with the club in a 2-4 home loss game against [[Paksi FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/nb-i-diosgyor-paks-2592345 |title=A Paks \u0151r\u00fcletes hib\u00e1kkal tark\u00edtott meccsen verte meg a DVTK-t|date=19 September 2017|publisher=www.nemzetisport.hu |language=hu}}</ref>\n\n===Mar\u00edtimo===\nOn 2 September 2018, the Portuguese club [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo|Mar\u00edtimo]] officially announced the signing of the Greek striker until the summer of 2021, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.gr/football/europe/article/1266264/episimo-toy-ioannidi-sti-maritimo |script-title=el:\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0399\u03c9\u03b1\u03bd\u03bd\u03af\u03b4\u03b7 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039c\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03c4\u03b9\u03bc\u03bf|language=el|date=2 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|31 October 2018}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align: center;\"\n\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=2|League\n!colspan=2|Cup\n!colspan=2|Others\n!colspan=2|Continental\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=2 valign=\"center\"|[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Superleague Greece|2012\u201313]]\n|0||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n!Total\n!0!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!1!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=2 valign=\"center\"|[[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]] (loan)\n|[[2013\u201314 3. Liga|2013\u201314]]\n|30||6||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||30||6\n|-\n!Total\n!30!!6!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!0!!0!!30!!6\n|-\n|rowspan=2 valign=\"center\"|[[PEC Zwolle]] (loan)\n|[[2014\u201315 Eredivisie|2014\u201315]]\n|4||0||2||0||1||0||1||0||8||0\n|-\n!Total\n!4!!0!!2!!0!!1!!0!!1!!0!!8!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=3 valign=\"center\"|[[Borussia Dortmund II]] (loan)\n|[[2014\u201315 3. Liga|2014\u201315]]\n|17||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||17||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 3. Liga|2015\u201316]]\n|6||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||6||1\n|-\n!Total\n!23!!2!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!0!!0!!23!!2\n|-\n|rowspa